We reiterated our recommendation in CY 2017 AAR, with modification, that the Municipal Accountant should: (a) prepare adjusting entry to drop from Accounts Payable unsubstantiated claims totaling P31,087,632.70 unless valid supporting documents are presented; 

and (b)  keep  the original file of the vouchers and its supporting documents pertaining to all recorded Accounts Payable until it is paid, and stop the practice of paying prior year’s obligations which were not recorded as Accounts Payable.

We further recommended that the Municipal Budget Officer stop the practice of releasing DVs to payees or suppliers and ensure that all the DVs which remained unpaid as of yearend, and duly obligated in the RAO, are transmitted to the Municipal Accountant before the agreed cut-off date to allow recording of the same in the books.

