We recommended that the Municipal Engineer in coordination with other
LGU officials concerned:
a. ensure the immediate completion of all on-going projects which
already have incurred delays;
b. include anticipated unworkable days in estimating the number of days
to complete a project to come up with a realistic project duration;
c. conduct regular monitoring and supervision of projects;
d. document any work extension orders/suspension orders, and,
e. impose liquidated damages on payments to contractors pursuant to
Item 8.1 of Annex “E” of the 2016 Revised IRR of RA No. 9184.

We recommend that the Municipal Mayor, as the Accountable Officer for
these cash advances, submit to the Audit Team the following:
1. Certified copies of the transmittal letter for the Liquidation Reports (LR)
of all previous cash advances duly stamped “received” by the ICFAU,
COA Central Office;
2. Certification of the Accountant that the SDO/Accountable Officer has no
unliquidated CF cash advances;
3. Basis for the computation of the appropriations for Confidential and
Intelligence Expenses considering that there was no specific fund
allocation for Peace and Order Program in the CY 2017 Annual Budget;
4. Valid justification on the following:
a.) Obtaining cash advances for confidential expenses even without the
approved POP by the MPOC and even without the Certification of the
PNP Chief on the peace and order situation of LGU Isabel;
b.) Grant of cash advances for confidential expenses for January to June
2017 or for six-month period, in excess of the three-month period
requirements;
